---
title: Docs UI overview
description:  This framework will act as a starting point for docs UI components.
---


This framework will act as a starting point for docs components.

It includes:

1. React.js
1. Carbon 10
1. Gatsby.js

## Prerequisites

Gatsby CLI

The Gatsby CLI tool lets you quickly create new Gatsby-powered sites and run commands for developing Gatsby sites. It is a published npm package.

The Gatsby CLI is available via npm and should be installed globally by running:

`npm install -g gatsby-cli`

## Getting started

1. Clone this repo
1. From directory root run `npm install` to install all dependencies
1. Run `npm run dev`
1. Head over to http://localhost:8000 to see your gatsby application running
